{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Dough","content":["Place 100 g water, sugar and yeast in mixing bowl then warm <nobr>2 min\/37°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, grease a large bowl with oil.","Add semolina, flour, salt and remaining 250 g water then knead <nobr>5 min\/<\/nobr>. Transfer dough to prepared bowl, cover with cling film then set aside to rise in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 1-2 hours). Towards end of rising time, prepare topping."]},{"title":"Topping","content":["Place pecorino cheese in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer half to a small bowl and set aside.","Add garlic and oil then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then heat <nobr>5 min\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add tomatoes, salt, basil and oregano then cook <nobr>10 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","On a lightly floured work surface, knead dough gently. Divide into 25 golf ball sized pieces then roll into circles (approx. Ø 10 cm). Cover with cling film and allow to rest for 15 minutes.","Heat a little oil in a frying pan then fry dough circles, 3-4 pieces at a time, over a medium-high heat, until cooked through (approx. 2-3 minutes) then drain on paper towels. Blot excess oil with paper towels then spread tomato sauce onto fried bases and sprinkle with reserved grated pecorino.","Serve immediately while still hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Dough","content":["350 g water","1 tsp sugar","1 tsp dried instant yeast","oil, for greasing","300 g semolina","300 g strong white bread flour, plus extra for flouring","2 tsp fine sea salt"]},{"title":"Topping","content":["100 g pecorino cheese, cut in pieces (3-4 cm)","1 garlic clove","30 g extra virgin olive oil","400 g tinned chopped tomatoes","1 tsp fine sea salt","2 sprigs fresh basil, leaves only","1 tsp dried oregano","oil, for frying"]}],"id":"r131875","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-9K30K1W1cpo\/XZanqu56n8I\/AAAAAAAAhCY\/Q6_XgpX7uXsHb9LjaBb